We reiterated and made supplemental recommendations and Management agree that the Local Chief Executive:

direct the LDRRMO, 

(i) together with the LDRRMC, to align LDRRM Plan for CY 2020 and thereafter with the LDRRMFIP prescribed by the above-quoted regulations; 

(ii) submit supplemental/amended AIP showing PPAs that were reprogrammed and were planned under the NDRRMF; and 

(iii) regularly monitor the implementation of projects out of the fund so as to avoid implementation of PPAs which are more appropriately chargeable against the General Fund;

enjoin all concerned officials to submit required documentations needed under item 1.15.b.ii of this memorandum, for further evaluation of the Audit Team;

instruct the Local Finance Committee to comply with the reporting requirements of the NDRRMF using the prescribed format as defined under item 4.2 of LBC 130.

to guarantee that only legitimate entitled beneficiaries will be given financial assistance, require the office of the Municipal Social Welfare Development (MSWD) to institutionalize the selection/screening procedures by formulating criteria and standards that will be used as management’s guidance in processing of applicants’ entitlement under the financial assistance program of the LGU.

We recommended that the Local Executive initiate/facilitate the disposal of unserviceable properties in accordance with the procedures mentioned above.

In addition, require the:

(a)	Human Resource Management Officer to assess/evaluate the available manpower complement of the Accounting, Engineering and General Services Office, in order to determine if additional manpower is needed in order to the facilitate the abovementioned requirements for PPEs;
(b)	Municipal Engineer to continue with the efforts initiated by setting a realistic or attainable yearly target in the coverage of initial inventory of local road networks in the Municipality in reference to the procedure set by COA Circular 2015-008 such as the rendition of reports to the Local Accountant and General Services Officer (GSO) with complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects;
(c)	Acting Municipal Accountant to (i) comply with the preparation and maintenance of Property Ledger Cards; (ii) keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components tor every road network; and (iii) prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of the depreciation tor each component at the end of the year; and
(d)	General Services Officer to (i) comply with the preparation and maintenance of Property Cards; (ii) prepare an Inventory and Inspection Unserviceable Report and Report of Waste Material, where applicable, for properties and request the same for disposal; and (iii) facilitate the conversion of vehicles with green plates to red plates and follow-up with concerned agencies the availability of government plates for newly acquired service vehicles.

